==获奖情况==
阿里·艾哈邁德·賽義德·伊斯比爾曾獲得[[布鲁塞尔文学奖|布鲁塞尔文学奖]]，[[土耳其|土耳其]][[希克梅特|希克梅特]]文学奖，[[马其顿|马其顿]]金冠诗歌奖，[[意大利|意大利]][[诺尼诺国际文学奖|诺尼诺国际文学奖]]等，近年也是[[诺贝尔文学奖|诺贝尔文学奖]]热门人选<ref name="McGrath">{{cite news|first=Charles|last=McGrath|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/18/books/18adonis.html|title=A Revolutionary of Arabic Verse|work=The New York Times|date=2010-10-17|access-date=2010-10-17|quote=Every year around this time the name of the Syrian poet Adonis pops up in newspapers and in betting shops. Adonis (pronounced ah-doh-NEES), a pseudonym adopted by Ali Ahmad Said Esber in his teens as an attention getter, is a perennial favorite to win the Nobel Prize in Literature.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|first=Diego Gómez|last=Pickering|url=http://www.forwardsyria.com/story/302/Adonis%20speaks%20to%20Forward:%20The%20living%20legend%20of%20Arab%20poetry|title=Adonis speaks to Forward: The living legend of Arab poetry|work=Forward|date=2010-11-11|access-date=2010-11-11|quote=Last month, Adonis was robbed again of a Nobel Prize, after first being nominated in 1988.|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101115062938/http://www.forwardsyria.com/story/302/Adonis%20speaks%20to%20Forward:%20The%20living%20legend%20of%20Arab%20poetry|archive-date=2010-11-15|url-status=dead}}</ref>。

==爭議==
===被阿拉伯作家聯盟除名===
1995年1月27日阿多尼斯被阿拉伯作家聯盟除名，理由是在1993年一次[[UNESCO|UNESCO]]主辦的會議上和以色列人見面。兩位敘利亞作家[[Saadallah_Wannous|Saadallah Wannous]]和[[Hanna_Mina|Hanna Mina]]為聲援阿多尼斯而自行退出阿拉伯作家聯盟。<ref>{{cite news|first=Youssef M.|last=Ibrahim|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1995/03/07/world/arabs-split-on-cultural-ties-to-israel.html|title=NYTimes: Arabs Split on Cultural Ties to Israel|work=The New York Times|date=1995-03-07}}</ref>

===死亡威脅===
阿多尼斯曾公開宣稱自己不信仰宗教並批判許多伊斯蘭教傳統。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/WriterArticles/NewsContentP/18/122235/Books/Aboutus.aspx|title=Adonis: ISIS and Nusra didn't fall from the sky}}</ref>埃及[[薩拉菲|薩拉菲]]教士Mohamad Said Raslan曾發布[[伊斯蘭教令|伊斯蘭教令]]要求刺殺阿多尼斯，因為他使用異教神話的名字當筆名。在一段視頻中<ref name=salafivideo>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=edUMeDifY1c|title=They are the enemy so watch out from them (translation from Arabic)}}</ref>Raslan控訴阿多尼斯反伊斯蘭，是異教徒，著作應當被禁。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NhFv36FTNWM|title=This is the ignorant Adonis - Sheikh Mohamed Said Raslan (Translation from Arabic)}}</ref>

2012年5月，一些[[叙利亚反对派|叙利亚反对派]]人士在[[Facebook|Facebook]]上鼓吹殺害阿多尼斯，因為他是[[阿拉維派|阿拉維派]]出身、曾批判伊斯蘭教、批评反对派并拒绝外国军事干预叙利亚。<ref name="dailystar.com.lb">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailystar.com.lb/Culture/Books/2012/May-18/173770-intellectuals-blast-syrian-opposition-calls-for-adonis-death.ashx|title=Intellectuals blast Syrian opposition calls for Adonis’ death}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.syriantelegraph.com/?p=12953|title=translation from Arabic to the title : a Syrian apposition group places Adonis on the "killing list" (Translation from Arabic)}}</ref>

===焚書===
2013年，伊斯蘭教學者Abdelfetah Zeraoui Hamadache在網上讀到一首署名阿多尼斯的詩之後，號召焚毀阿多尼斯的著作。<ref>Adonis: fatwa calling for burning my books in Algeria is shameful http://www.echoroukonline.com/ara/mobile/articles/189272.html{{Dead link|date=August 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>Les salafistes algériens du Front de la Sahwa en campagne contre "le parti de la France" http://www.huffpostmaghreb.com/2014/05/30/salafistes-algeriens-camp_n_5415386.html {{Wayback|url=http://www.huffpostmaghreb.com/2014/05/30/salafistes-algeriens-camp_n_5415386.html |date=20180921034417 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://elhayat.net/article773.html|title=elhayat Article in Arabic titled (translation) "Hamadache judges Adonis as an infidel and calls for burning his books}}</ref>但該詩後來被證明是冒用阿多尼斯的名義。<ref>In a phone interview with "Echorouk Newspaper" published on 23 December 2013</ref><ref>Adonis: fatwa calling for burning my books in Algeria is shameful http://www.echoroukonline.com/ara/articles/189272.html?print</ref>

===阿拉伯之春===
2011年6月11日，阿多尼斯在黎巴嫩報紙上發表公開信，批判敘利亞總統[[巴沙尔·阿萨德|巴沙尔·阿萨德]]的暴力統治並要求他下台。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://assafir.com/Article/241058|title=Adonis, "Open Letter to President Bashar al-Assad; Man, His Basic Rights and Freedoms, or the Abyss," As-Safir, Beirut, June 14, 2011}}</ref>同年8月他接受科威特報紙訪問時重申了這一要求。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.monstersandcritics.com/middleeast/news/article_1655371.php/Prominent-Syrian-poet-Adunis-calls-on-Assad-to-step-down|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120717114832/http://news.monstersandcritics.com/middleeast/news/article_1655371.php/Prominent-Syrian-poet-Adunis-calls-on-Assad-to-step-down|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2012-07-17|title=Prominent Syrian poet Adunis calls on Assad to step down|work=Monsters and Critics|date=2011-08-06|accessdate=2011-08-06}}</ref>他同時呼籲反對派避免暴力並和政府對話。<ref>[https://www.economist.com/news/special-report/21580628-after-revolution-comes-slow-business-devising-machinery-change-long "Constitution-building: The long march"], "The Economist", 13 July 2013.</ref>

==与中国的关系==
1980年曾到访[[北京|北京]]，2009年第二次到[[中国|中国]]。他被人评为“阿拉伯世界的鲁迅”。<ref>《南方人物周刊》2009.4.20</ref>在大陆出版有诗集《[[我的孤独是一座花园|我的孤独是一座花园]]》，[[薛庆国|薛庆国]]译，[[译林出版社|译林出版社]]，2009年。

